##Asymptomatic patients also have the potential to spread! New Coronaviruses look more like flu than SARS, according to a study published in top medical journals

The development of the epidemic situation of new coronavirus is changing rapidly all over the world.

As of 9:00 a.m. on February 24, there were zero new confirmed cases in 23 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) throughout the day, according to the official release of provincial health committees, including Beijing, Hunan, Henan, Tianjin and so on.

In Italy, the country's first death from new pneumonia prompted the country to announce on February 21st that it would close public places in several northern cities. As of midnight local time on the 24th, the total number of confirmed cases in Italy reached 157, the European pneumonia epidemic is currently the most serious country. Now, 11 towns in northern Italy have been sealed off, schools have been closed, and a series of events including carnival and football matches have been cancelled. Violators could face up to three months in prison or a fine of up to 206 euros.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Medics in Codogno, Italy, replenish new beds (CNN)

As of the afternoon of February 23,169 new cases had been confirmed in South Korea, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 602 and the death toll to five, Yonhap reported. South Korean President Moon jae-in 23, said the new pneumonia epidemic warning level from the current "alert" to the highest "serious" level. South Korea's prime minister, Chung Sye-kyun, urged all citizens to suspend religious activities and other activities that are held indoors or in crowded outdoor areas, and said the government would act in accordance with the law and principles, deal sternly with those who obstruct the government's epidemic prevention work, hoarding and gathering in public places to make others feel uneasy.

Similarly, new coronavirus infection in Japan is also expanding. As of midnight on February 24, the cumulative number of confirmed cases in 16 prefecture of Japan districts in Japan stood at 129. In addition, the number of infections not linked to China is increasing, and the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare and the autonomous communities continue to conduct follow up investigations. But if you add the confirmed cases from the diamond princess in Port of Yokohama, which added 57 cases on February 23, more than 800 people in the country have been confirmed with the disease.

According to foreign media reports, the new crown pneumonia epidemic in the Middle East countries also began to spread. Kianush Jahanpur, a spokesman for Iran's Ministry of Health, announced on February 23 that Iran had 15 new confirmed cases of pneumonia that day, bringing the total number of cases to 43, with eight deaths. To prevent further spread of the disease, the Iranian government has ordered the closure of schools in 14 provinces, including Tehran Province, while suspending cultural and sports activities. Iran's Health Ministry also called for a halt to all religious gatherings in the hard hit region of Qom. As one of the holy cities of the Shiites, Qom is flooded with pilgrims every year.

In addition, the spread of the new coronavirus has reached the United Arab Emirates, Israel and Lebanon. The United Arab Emirates Ministry of Health announced on February 21 that a Filipino and a Bangladeshi were infected with the new coronavirus, bringing the total number of cases in the country to 11. Israel also confirmed the country's first case on the 21st, after the patient was evacuated from the "Diamond Princess" cruise ship by plane back to Israel. Lebanon became the latest country in the Middle East to be hit by the outbreak after a returnee from Iran was diagnosed.

On Friday, the World Health Organization Organization warned that "the window of opportunity to contain a global outbreak of COVID-19 is narrowing" , and on the same day, the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) warned that COVID-19 was "highly likely" to spread in the United States. CDC National Center for Immunization and Respiratory Disease Director Dr. Mason Neil told reporters that U.S. health officials are preparing for a coronavirus "pandemic. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Image | Mason Neil, Ph. D

"So far, we haven't seen a spread of the virus in the American community, but it's very likely that it will even happen eventually, " she said. For now, our goal remains to control the spread of the virus in the United States, which will buy us more time to prepare for more cases and possible continued transmission, "If that day comes, we will have to shut down schools and businesses like China, " she added

Is the new coronavirus more like the flu than SARS?

Infectious disease experts had previously predicted a possible future for the disease: COVID-19 might not disappear, or it might become another common virus.

Wang Chen, vice president of the Chinese Academy of Engineering and an expert in respiratory and critical care medicine, also told CCTV: "We may have to prepare for the long-term coexistence of the new coronavirus, which may turn into a chronic, influenza-like disease that has long existed in the human world. It is a possibility, and we need to be prepared for it."

This view is supported by a recent paper in The The New England Journal of Medicine, which for The first time reveals a dynamic change in The viral load of The New coronavirus in patients with symptoms. The results of the study may suggest that the changes in the human body are more similar to COVID-19 than to SARS, which is more closely related to the virus.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure | screenshot of the paper (Source: Nejm)

The study was conducted by researchers from the Guangdong Provincial Center for Disease Control and Prevention, the Fifth Affiliated Hospital of the National Sun Yat-sen University, and the University of Hong Kong, the researchers monitored new coronavirus loads in respiratory specimens from 18 confirmed cases (9 males, 9 females, median age 59 years, age range 26-76 years) in Zhuhai, Guangdong Province, the relationship between viral load and disease progression was analyzed.

The study sample included four patients with secondary infections in two family clusters, one of whom had never developed symptoms and who had been in close contact with patients with known confirmed cases and were therefore monitored. A total of 72 NASAL SWABS (from the middle turbinate and NASOPHARYNX) and 72 pharyngeal swabs were analyzed, one to nine times per patient; all patients were swabbed with a polyfoam swab during the study.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure | viral load: figure a shows the cyclic threshold (CT) value of Orf1b in reverse transcriptase-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) analysis, which was detected in nasal swab samples from 14 imported cases and 3 secondary cases Figure B shows the CT value of the throat Swab (Source: Nejm) 

The researchers analyzed the viral load in nasal and pharyngeal swabs from 17 symptomatic patients in relation to the day of onset of symptoms. They found that patients had a higher viral load (inversely proportional to the CT value) shortly after the onset of symptoms, with a higher load in the nose than in the throat. In their analysis, the researchers concluded that the pattern of nucleic acid shedding in patients infected with the new coronavirus was similar to that in type 4 flu patients, and appeared to be different from those infected with SARS during SARS.

In addition, the study found that the viral load detected in samples from asymptomatic patients was very close to that of symptomatic patients, suggesting that both asymptomatic and mildly symptomatic patients have the potential for transmission, and may have a strong infectivity in the early stage of infection. At the same time, the researchers also suggest that in contrast to the SARS prevention and control strategy, now to make some changes to strengthen the new pneumonia patients with early diagnosis and isolation. Because the SARS virus mainly occurs in a few days after the outbreak, and in the early outbreak of respiratory viral load is not much, when symptoms appear about 10 days will reach the peak viral load. The COVID-19, on the other hand, needs to be treated with caution from an early age.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure | relationship between viral load and Symptom Onset Day (Nejm)

But at the end of the paper, the researchers stressed that more research is needed to analyze the relationship between viral load and COVID-19. At the same time, viral RNA was detectable in Oropharyngeal samples from patients with mild and asymptomatic diseases for at least five days, suggesting that the team needed more and better data to further determine the dynamics of viral transmission, in order to be able to screen for research practice can provide effective information on the sample.

Global Cooling with this heat?

Earlier, as the epidemic spread, prejudice and discrimination also began to spread in certain corners of individual countries. As the outbreak in China has been brought under control, and as it has spread rapidly in other countries, the debate has also erupted online over whether China's efforts would be in vain if the new coronavirus were to spread globally.

Objectively, there will be an impact. The new coronavirus, which is so contagious, embodies the spirit of a "community of shared future, " Chinese leader Xi Jinping said in a letter to Bill Gates, co-chairman of the Gates Foundation, "mankind is a community of destiny. Unity and cooperation are the most powerful weapons in the fight against an epidemic that affects the safety and security of all peoples. "

Similarly, World Health Organization Director General Tan Desai said at a press conference: This epidemic is testing us in many ways. It is a test of global political solidarity, a test of whether the world can unite to fight a common "enemy" that transcends national boundaries and ideologies, and a test of global financial solidarity, a test of whether the world is investing now in the fight against the epidemic, or whether it is not investing enough to pay more later to deal with its consequences, and finally, a test of Global Scientific Solidarity, it tests whether the world's scientific community can come together to find answers to common challenges.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure | who director-general Tan Desai (Twitter)

At present, more than pharmaceutical companies around the world have invested in the development and testing of vaccines and other drugs. Similarly, many researchers are also working hard to analyze the epidemic from multiple perspectives. For the general public, during the period when society is gradually returning to work and normalizing, it is necessary to recognize an objective fact: The situation of epidemic prevention is still very serious, if we are not careful, a single disseminator may cause a group of people around us to be infected; similarly, the pressure on health care workers in the hard-hit areas remains enormous.

Therefore, the moment of resuming work is the key moment of epidemic prevention. The long-term atmosphere of public opinion and media reports may have caused many people who are concerned about the epidemic to enter a period of mental fatigue, but that doesn't mean people can go out shopping, dating, or dining out without consideration and protection. The statistics we see every day can not be reduced to statistics, especially the number of deaths. "We have to remember that these are people, not numbers, " Tan said

I hope you can be responsible to yourself, to others, to minimize unnecessary contact, but also to avoid unnecessary gathering.
